President Donald Trump delivered a speech in Miami, Florida, outlining his new policy towards Cuba. In his speech, he expressed sympathy for the victims of the Castro regime and criticized the previous administration's approach to Cuba. He announced that he would be canceling the previous administration's deal with Cuba and implementing stricter restrictions on travel and trade with the country. He also called on the Cuban government to release political prisoners and respect human rights. Trump emphasized that the United States would always stand for liberty and support the Cuban people in their struggle for freedom. The speech marked the two-year anniversary of his announcement to run for president.